  "title": "Conversations, Act One: Exiles at the Sandbar",
  "summary": "At Plaxton's rebuilt Sandbar on Caspar, Keifan sits drinking heavily when Doctor Lynae Caiton joins him and confronts him about both his self-destructive drinking and a dangerous new 'venture' against an organization called Maffi. Their tense, intimate argument reveals that the two are former Imperials, recently exiled after swearing a forced oath rather than dying, and Lynae bears a rewired pacemaker implanted as punishment that will eventually kill her. A starfighter pilot named Jamon eavesdrops, growing angry as he pieces together their Imperial past and warns them not to bring their demons to his home. Mid-confrontation Lynae's implant triggers a near-fatal cardiac episode and she collapses; Keifan, with Jamon's help fetching vials from his coat, administers an emergency injection that revives her. The act ends with Lynae shaken and embarrassed on the floor and Jamon, contrite, asking how he can make amends.",
